WEBVTT

00:02.020 --> 00:04.860
- Bring me the flash drive.
- I haven't got it. Renko took it.
It's gone.

00:04.860 --> 00:06.939
- We cut her a deal. If she can
bring you down,

00:06.939 --> 00:08.940
then her child stays out of prison.

00:08.940 --> 00:11.380
- Did my dad rape you?
- Yes.

00:11.380 --> 00:13.180
- But if you go to prison,

00:13.180 --> 00:16.980
then your family will have to face
what's coming without you.

00:16.980 --> 00:18.700
- So what's taking so long?

00:18.700 --> 00:21.100
- There's nothing to suggest that
Hicks killed Butler.

00:21.100 --> 00:22.780
- He's sleeping with the man's wife.

00:22.780 --> 00:25.740
- Do you think he killed your
husband?
- Of course he didn't! Jesus!

00:25.740 --> 00:27.900
- For what it's worth, I don't think
so, either.

00:27.900 --> 00:30.620
- She told someone where it is and
what to do with it,

00:30.620 --> 00:33.660
someone she can trust, but I don't
know who that is.

00:33.660 --> 00:35.580
- When she was 14,

00:35.580 --> 00:39.340
Renko's parents brought in a
complaint of rape against a teacher.

00:39.340 --> 00:41.140
Noah Underhill.

00:44.060 --> 00:46.700
[LABOURED BREATHING]

00:50.140 --> 00:52.900
[DISTANT SIREN]

00:54.000 --> 01:00.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:23.380 --> 01:24.860
- Do you want to buy some dope?

01:24.860 --> 01:26.460
Hey! Oi!

02:24.460 --> 02:27.180
[HIS BREATHING BEGINS TO SETTLE]

02:40.700 --> 02:43.020
[HE GROANS IN PAIN]

02:46.420 --> 02:48.580
- Stop! Please!

03:03.900 --> 03:05.900
- Hello, Dad.

04:40.420 --> 04:42.260
[HE CLEARS HIS THROAT]

04:51.740 --> 04:53.660
Morning.

04:53.660 --> 04:56.540
You fancy a cooked breakfast? Come
on, I'm starving here.

04:58.300 --> 05:00.580
- No, I couldn't, babe. Just woke
up.

05:00.580 --> 05:03.220
- Oh, come on, have a proper
breakfast.

05:03.220 --> 05:04.980
I'll do the full works, how's that?

05:13.260 --> 05:16.180
[RUMBLE OF TRAINS]

05:39.060 --> 05:40.940
- Have you found your son?

05:40.940 --> 05:42.580
- No, sir.

05:42.580 --> 05:44.620
- And he's been missing how long?

05:44.620 --> 05:47.060
- Just over a week.

05:47.060 --> 05:50.100
- And you've been looking for him?
- Very hard, yeah.

05:52.380 --> 05:55.700
- Your son is the sword that I've
got dangling over your head,

05:55.700 --> 05:59.100
and then suddenly he's gone -
bazinga! Penn and Teller,

05:59.100 --> 06:00.900
disappeared into a puff of magic.

06:00.900 --> 06:03.340
- There was nothing magic about it,
I can tell you that much.

06:03.340 --> 06:05.620
- So you didn't suggest to him that
he slice himself up

06:05.620 --> 06:07.980
- and get himself sent to hospital?
- Why would I do that?

06:07.980 --> 06:09.980
- Cos it's a lot easier for your boy
to

06:09.980 --> 06:12.580
escape from a hospital than a secure
unit.

06:12.580 --> 06:15.100
And once he's free, so are you,

06:15.100 --> 06:17.420
of me, of Hicks.

06:17.420 --> 06:19.980
- That's not what happened.
- Then what did?
- I don't know.

06:19.980 --> 06:22.580
I'll tell you when I find him.

06:24.980 --> 06:27.060
- Choose a side, Elaine.

06:27.060 --> 06:30.020
- All right, I'll choose a side when
you tell me what this is all about.

06:30.020 --> 06:32.620
Because we both know that Hicks
didn't kill Alex Butler.

06:32.620 --> 06:35.660
So, come on. Why do you want him so
badly?

06:35.660 --> 06:38.100
- What, you still think this is
about me?

06:38.100 --> 06:40.980
That I'm set on revenge because
Charlie Hicks shtupped my wife

06:40.980 --> 06:42.900
at the Christmas party?

06:42.900 --> 06:46.620
Well, I don't have a wife. I have a
husband.

06:46.620 --> 06:50.420
And none of this has got anything to
do with me and what I want.

06:50.420 --> 06:52.780
This comes from above my head.

06:52.780 --> 06:56.420
Someone on high wants Charlie Hicks
defenestrated.

06:56.420 --> 06:58.740
- Who on high?
- [KNOCKING AT DOOR]

06:58.740 --> 07:01.620
- Sorry, guv. Got a call.
- That's fine.

07:01.620 --> 07:04.460
I think DI Renko and I have gone
through this morning's agenda.

07:04.460 --> 07:06.260
- Yeah. Thank you, sir.

07:08.380 --> 07:10.700
- What have we got?
- Victim's a Noah Underhill.

07:17.580 --> 07:19.540
- OK?
- Yeah.

07:21.060 --> 07:23.300
- I'm out the door. Send details.
- On their way.

07:35.580 --> 07:37.180
- Morning, sir.
- Morning.

07:38.980 --> 07:41.180
[RADIO CHATTER]

07:44.180 --> 07:46.100
What, that bad?

07:58.980 --> 08:00.980
- Morning, Keith.
- Boss.

08:06.220 --> 08:08.140
- He's divorced, lives alone.

08:08.140 --> 08:10.860
We think the killer broke into the
house while he was out running.

08:10.860 --> 08:14.100
- He liked to run at night. Which is
a thing people do, apparently...

08:14.100 --> 08:15.980
..for reasons.

08:18.700 --> 08:20.420
The...

08:22.500 --> 08:24.380
The killer took an ice pick to...

08:26.340 --> 08:29.140
- His genitals, Keith. You can say
it.

08:29.140 --> 08:32.340
The killer took an ice pick to the
victim's penis and testicles.

08:34.260 --> 08:36.059
- Well, someone was miffed.

08:37.059 --> 08:39.539
- I mean, why cant we all just get
along and stop ice-picking

08:39.539 --> 08:41.940
- each other's wing-wangs?
- [THEY CHUCKLE]

08:48.860 --> 08:50.340
Have we got a name?

08:50.340 --> 08:52.860
- Underhill. First name, Noah.

08:57.980 --> 09:00.300
- Where's Elaine?
- She's on her way.

09:00.300 --> 09:03.260
The guvnor called her in for a talk.

09:03.260 --> 09:05.220
- Listen, just... Just give me a
tick.

09:12.060 --> 09:14.540
[MOBILE PHONE RINGS]

09:17.220 --> 09:20.300
- DCI Hicks.
- He's a tinker, isn't he?

09:22.300 --> 09:25.860
- Who is?
- Elaine's boy, Daniel, who do you
think?

09:27.780 --> 09:31.460
- What have you done?
- I mean, an ice pick to the
privates.

09:31.460 --> 09:33.660
That's got to be a "ten from Len".

09:35.740 --> 09:40.100
- Wait a minute. Are you here? Are
you watching this?

09:40.100 --> 09:43.500
- Listen to me, Charlie. Stop
looking for me and listen.

09:43.500 --> 09:46.460
We turned the place over before the
first responders got to the scene,

09:46.460 --> 09:48.780
but we couldn't find the flash
drive.

09:48.780 --> 09:51.260
Oh. Here comes trouble.

10:08.340 --> 10:10.540
Elaine's about to do all she can to
save her child.

10:10.540 --> 10:12.380
She will dig her own grave in the
process.

10:12.380 --> 10:14.420
All you have to do is get that flash
drive

10:14.420 --> 10:17.660
and she is out of our lives, safely,
with no more blood shed.

10:17.660 --> 10:20.700
- Fuck, I can't just go blundering
about into a crime scene.

10:20.700 --> 10:24.020
- Well, if it were me, I would
follow Elaine.

10:24.020 --> 10:26.060
She must know where it's hidden.

10:26.060 --> 10:28.100
Just let her find it and take it
from her.

10:28.100 --> 10:30.780
- And then what? What happens to
Elaine?

10:30.780 --> 10:33.300
- She's trying to hang you, Charlie.

10:33.300 --> 10:35.780
Just let her hang herself instead.

10:35.780 --> 10:37.900
- Anyway, I've got to go.

10:37.900 --> 10:40.340
- Hey.
- So, what are we looking at?

10:51.420 --> 10:54.060
Morning.
- How's it going?
- Yeah, tip-top.

11:01.460 --> 11:05.260
- Do we know what he did for a
living?
- He was a personal tutor.
- For?

11:05.260 --> 11:08.860
- Rich people with dense kids.
- Any funny business?

11:08.860 --> 11:11.740
You know, with his... pupils?

11:13.060 --> 11:15.260
- Nothing that we know of.
- But that doesn't mean no.

11:15.260 --> 11:18.020
And revenge for sexual assault would
explain the winkle.

11:18.020 --> 11:19.980
- Any forensics?

11:19.980 --> 11:21.780
- Nice trainer print outside, size
8,

11:21.780 --> 11:25.140
but other than that, he was pretty
cautious.

11:25.140 --> 11:29.140
- He? We like someone for it?

11:29.140 --> 11:31.460
- Not yet, no.
- So it's not necessarily a he.

11:31.460 --> 11:33.540
- Well, she'd have to be a strong
woman.

11:33.540 --> 11:36.540
- What, and women can't be strong?
- Yeah, Keith, check your privilege.

11:36.540 --> 11:39.180
- My wife won't let me.
- And nothing was taken?

11:39.180 --> 11:41.820
- Well, the place has been turned
over, but his computer's still

11:41.820 --> 11:44.020
here, the TV, the DVD player.

11:44.020 --> 11:46.380
Haven't found the victim's phone
yet, though.

11:46.380 --> 11:47.860
- So the killer took it?

11:47.860 --> 11:50.220
- If he did, he had the presence of
mind to power it down.

11:50.220 --> 11:52.580
- So it won't be much use without
the password, then?

11:52.580 --> 11:54.460
- Fingerprint detection's
capacitive.

11:54.460 --> 11:57.060
Even if the victim's bleeding out,
the killer could have

11:57.060 --> 11:59.860
used his fingerprint, unlocked the
phone, and reset the password.

11:59.860 --> 12:03.100
- Either way, the second he powers
up that phone, we'll have him.

12:03.100 --> 12:05.100
- OK, good.

14:05.660 --> 14:08.260
Well, hello there. George.

14:13.100 --> 14:15.620
[MOBILE PHONE VIBRATES] George.

14:15.620 --> 14:17.500
- Boss, the victim's phone's been
powered up.

14:17.500 --> 14:20.460
- Nice one. Listen, patch it
through, all right?

14:21.980 --> 14:24.020
He's turned on the phone.

14:24.020 --> 14:25.580
We've got him.

14:31.940 --> 14:34.820
- How long is this going to take?
- Herbie?

14:34.820 --> 14:37.820
- Not long. We know the phone's
still in London.

14:37.820 --> 14:39.820
We're triangulating the signal now.

14:52.300 --> 14:54.900
And... boom. Got him.

14:56.340 --> 14:58.100
He's in here somewhere.

14:59.620 --> 15:01.660
Sending you the feeds now.

15:06.820 --> 15:09.500
- What about this scabby little
nutsack?

15:10.820 --> 15:13.340
- Herbie, can you zoom into the
blonde kid playing on his phone?

15:13.340 --> 15:15.300
- There.
- Moving in.

15:45.780 --> 15:47.500
[PHONE PINGS]

15:53.580 --> 15:55.060
- What's he doing?

15:55.060 --> 15:57.940
- Herbie, has he seen something?
Have you got uniforms on the scene?

15:57.940 --> 15:59.820
- Not yet. Officers are en route.

16:07.060 --> 16:09.580
Phone's off. We can still keep eyes
on him.

16:39.380 --> 16:42.460
Lost him. Sorry.

16:47.980 --> 16:50.420
Boss, can I have a word?

16:50.420 --> 16:52.340
- Yeah, of course.

16:52.340 --> 16:54.660
- What, now?
- Yeah, outside.

17:05.099 --> 17:07.819
I just got a text. It's about my
son, Daniel.

17:07.819 --> 17:09.660
Sorry, I'll have to sit this one
out.

17:13.780 --> 17:15.940
- Is he OK?
- Not really, no.

17:19.540 --> 17:22.099
- Well, I need you here.
- Yeah, I know.

17:22.099 --> 17:23.740
But he comes first.

17:29.220 --> 17:31.100
- Yeah, yeah, sure.

17:31.100 --> 17:33.900
Listen, you do what you've got to
do.
- Right, cheers, boss.

17:33.900 --> 17:35.620
I'll make up the time.

18:06.060 --> 18:09.020
[SHE WHIMPERS QUIETLY]

18:29.860 --> 18:32.860
[SHE BREATHES ERRATICALLY]

19:05.220 --> 19:07.860
- You can relax now, Charlie. I
think we can take it from here.

19:07.860 --> 19:10.100
- She hasn't got it. Her son's got
it. Daniel.

19:12.380 --> 19:15.100
Listen, Elaine's trying to get to
him before the police can.

19:15.100 --> 19:17.900
She is on her last nerves here, so
let me handle this.

19:19.980 --> 19:22.580
- Because she trusts you?

19:24.740 --> 19:27.820
- I wouldn't call it that.

19:27.820 --> 19:29.820
- You should be working for us.

19:29.820 --> 19:31.700
- All right, there's no need to get
nasty.

19:31.700 --> 19:33.380
- It's a genuine offer.

19:33.380 --> 19:36.460
We'll need people like you in the
days to come.

19:36.460 --> 19:38.340
- And what is to come?

19:38.340 --> 19:40.700
Eh? What is it?

19:46.580 --> 19:49.540
- Do you ever read the Bible?

19:49.540 --> 19:51.220
- Only the rude bits.

19:54.020 --> 19:59.140
- "And I looked and behold a pale
horse, and his name that sat on him

19:59.140 --> 20:01.500
"was Death."

20:03.580 --> 20:05.300
"And Hell followed with him."

20:09.980 --> 20:12.140
- Then why does it even matter?

20:12.140 --> 20:13.380
Hmm?

20:14.820 --> 20:16.260
The file and Elaine?

20:17.700 --> 20:21.540
Cos whatever you do, people are
going to know eventually.

20:22.580 --> 20:23.980
- I made a promise.

20:23.980 --> 20:25.220
- What, to the Government?

20:25.220 --> 20:26.500
[HE SCOFFS]

20:26.500 --> 20:29.220
- Sod the Government.
- It's not about the Government.

20:31.900 --> 20:35.420
I just want to hang on to this for
as long as I can, Charlie.

20:37.540 --> 20:38.940
Normality.

20:41.060 --> 20:44.660
I just want to treasure what we've
got, while we've got it.

20:49.460 --> 20:51.660
- You just keep your people out of
my way.

20:52.940 --> 20:55.540
I'll get you your flash drive. And
then we're done.

21:08.260 --> 21:11.460
[VIDEO GAME SOUND EFFECTS]

21:13.300 --> 21:15.060
[DOORBELL RINGS]

21:30.460 --> 21:31.940
- Simone! Hi!

21:31.940 --> 21:34.820
- Hi. Sorry, have you got five
minutes?

21:36.020 --> 21:38.420
- Yeah, yeah, of course. Come on in.

21:38.420 --> 21:41.700
Oh, my God! Oh, congratulations!

21:41.700 --> 21:42.780
- Thanks.

21:42.780 --> 21:44.940
- I mean, come in! Put your feet up.

21:44.940 --> 21:46.340
- Hey, I've brought cake.
- Oh!

21:54.500 --> 21:56.780
- I'm sorry I haven't been round.

21:56.780 --> 21:59.580
You give someone space because you
think they probably need it.

21:59.580 --> 22:01.580
Then, before you know it, months
have gone past

22:01.580 --> 22:04.300
and you feel like you've abandoned
them.

22:04.300 --> 22:06.220
- Nobody abandoned anyone.

22:06.220 --> 22:08.820
Life moves on. Takes you with it.

22:10.060 --> 22:11.780
- But you still see 'em? The others?

22:12.980 --> 22:15.260
- Sometimes, yeah. Erm...

22:15.260 --> 22:18.860
Keith makes the effort, drops round
the odd shepherd's pie.

22:18.860 --> 22:21.140
Erm, Herbie, sometimes.

22:22.420 --> 22:23.900
It's hard for them, you know.

22:25.780 --> 22:30.740
They see me and then they see this
absence, next to me.

22:31.980 --> 22:34.620
- And Charlie? When's the last time
you saw him?

22:36.620 --> 22:37.900
- I don't know, really.

22:37.900 --> 22:39.260
- But you do still see him?

22:40.900 --> 22:43.500
- Yeah. Sometimes. I mean - yeah.

22:47.100 --> 22:51.340
- The reason I ask is cos every time
I mention your name...

22:52.780 --> 22:56.540
..ask how you're doing or whatever,
he... he clams up.

22:57.980 --> 22:59.380
He won't talk about you.

23:02.780 --> 23:04.620
But I know he cares about you.

23:07.900 --> 23:09.900
- Yeah, I know he does.

23:09.900 --> 23:11.300
I know he cares about us.

23:12.740 --> 23:18.060
- It's just, the thing about Charlie
- he likes to look after people.

23:19.500 --> 23:21.700
It's like a nervous compulsion.

23:22.740 --> 23:24.700
And you mean so much to him.

23:24.700 --> 23:26.140
And he loves you.

23:27.300 --> 23:28.980
But he thinks he let you down.

23:30.500 --> 23:33.140
You, Alex and Owen.

23:34.780 --> 23:36.300
- But that's not true.

23:37.820 --> 23:38.940
He didn't.

23:40.580 --> 23:42.700
- Could you just...

23:42.700 --> 23:45.980
..look him in the eye and tell him
it wasn't his fault?

23:48.020 --> 23:50.060
Alex...

23:50.060 --> 23:52.540
He died and it... it was horrible.

23:54.620 --> 23:56.420
But it wasn't his fault.

24:07.020 --> 24:08.700
[KNOCKING]

24:11.860 --> 24:15.660
- Fran? Hi, I'm Gretchen Ross from
Social Services.

24:15.660 --> 24:16.980
We spoke on the phone.

24:18.660 --> 24:20.220
About Daniel Renko?

24:20.220 --> 24:23.140
- Oh, of course, yes. Come in.

24:23.140 --> 24:25.700
- You'll have to excuse the mess.
- Oh, not at all.

24:29.780 --> 24:32.340
So what can you tell me about
Daniel?

24:32.340 --> 24:34.460
You were his last foster family?

24:34.460 --> 24:37.460
- That's right.
- How was he? How did he fit in?

24:39.340 --> 24:43.140
- Look, there's usually a honeymoon
period

24:43.140 --> 24:45.460
where a child is sizing you up.

24:45.460 --> 24:48.140
It can be a very anxious time.

24:49.540 --> 24:52.740
Rejection or abuse by the birth
mother has proved

24:52.740 --> 24:55.900
that they're not worth loving. Not
worth trusting.

24:55.900 --> 24:58.140
Not worth much of anything, really.

24:59.460 --> 25:00.980
So they act out, trying to

25:00.980 --> 25:04.660
end a placement before someone else
takes it away from them.

25:04.660 --> 25:07.580
They're disruptive and violent.

25:07.580 --> 25:12.020
They set fires. Start fights.
Self-medicate.

25:15.180 --> 25:17.660
- And Daniel acted out like that?

25:17.660 --> 25:19.940
- He was a very damaged boy.

25:21.180 --> 25:22.540
We tried our best.

25:22.540 --> 25:24.420
But he needed more than we could
give.

25:25.780 --> 25:29.860
- You are aware that Daniel recently
got placed in a secure unit?

25:29.860 --> 25:33.220
- Apparently. I think he attacked
his birth mother?

25:33.220 --> 25:35.580
- That's right.
- How is she?

25:36.860 --> 25:39.420
- She's fine. She'll be OK.

25:39.420 --> 25:41.220
- I'm glad to hear she's all right.

25:44.580 --> 25:47.220
- Just over a week ago, Daniel
absconded.

25:47.220 --> 25:49.780
Is there anything you can tell us
that might help find him?

25:49.780 --> 25:52.260
A place he'd go? A friend he'd rely
on?

25:52.260 --> 25:54.940
- Not really. Sorry.

25:54.940 --> 25:57.860
He was very private. He barely
spoke.

26:06.460 --> 26:09.220
Actually, there was a place.

26:10.780 --> 26:12.500
Somewhere he'd run to, basically,

26:12.500 --> 26:14.900
back when he was with his previous
family.

26:14.900 --> 26:17.980
- And... And where was that? Do
you... Do you remember?

27:34.420 --> 27:36.100
[BIRDS FLUTTER]

27:43.660 --> 27:45.260
- I know why you did it.

27:46.540 --> 27:50.580
It wasn't right, but I get it.

27:55.420 --> 27:56.700
- How'd you find me?

28:01.020 --> 28:02.540
- It's my job to find people.

28:02.540 --> 28:05.300
- Is that why you're here, then? For
your job?

28:05.300 --> 28:07.180
- No.

28:07.180 --> 28:10.620
- He was a rapist. He deserved it.

28:10.620 --> 28:12.220
- I know, but that's not how it
works.

28:12.220 --> 28:13.500
- It should be.

28:13.500 --> 28:15.100
- Some people think so, yeah.

28:16.540 --> 28:17.900
- But not you.

28:18.940 --> 28:20.460
- No. Not me.

28:24.100 --> 28:25.500
- He gave me something.

28:31.820 --> 28:35.260
He was lying on the floor. He was
bleeding.

28:35.260 --> 28:38.220
He said, "I know why you're here."
And he sent me to get this.

28:40.100 --> 28:41.420
- Have you looked at it?

28:41.420 --> 28:42.700
- Why?

28:42.700 --> 28:44.300
- Have you? Have you looked at it?

28:46.780 --> 28:48.220
- No.

28:48.220 --> 28:49.500
What is it?

28:49.500 --> 28:51.220
- Look, it doesn't matter.

28:51.220 --> 28:54.060
- So, are you here for me? Or you
here for this?

28:54.060 --> 28:56.980
- I'm here for you, Daniel. I'm here
to help you.

28:56.980 --> 28:58.940
[BIRD FLUTTERS AND CHEEPS]

29:02.460 --> 29:04.180
- Come on!
- No!

29:04.180 --> 29:05.580
- Daniel, run!

29:06.620 --> 29:08.180
[DANIEL SHOUTS]

29:08.180 --> 29:10.140
- Charlie! Let him go.

29:10.140 --> 29:11.860
- I get the flash drive

29:11.860 --> 29:15.220
and we forget I ever clapped eyes on
Jack the Ripper here.

29:15.220 --> 29:17.420
Everyone's laughing.

29:17.420 --> 29:19.220
- You're doing this for them?

29:19.220 --> 29:21.340
- No, Elaine. My kids.

29:21.340 --> 29:23.900
- You think you're putting your
family first but you're not.

29:23.900 --> 29:26.020
- Tell him to give me the flash
drive!

29:26.020 --> 29:28.100
Or I'll break his arm.

29:28.100 --> 29:29.380
Tell him!

29:32.020 --> 29:34.460
- I saw the file you gave him.

29:34.460 --> 29:36.460
How else did he get it?

29:36.460 --> 29:38.220
- You do what you've got to.

29:38.220 --> 29:39.540
- But you were wrong.

29:40.860 --> 29:42.580
Noah wasn't Daniel's father.

29:45.740 --> 29:46.940
- Bullshit.

29:46.940 --> 29:49.220
- My parents thought he was.

29:49.220 --> 29:51.940
But he wasn't. He was a good man.

29:53.140 --> 29:55.180
He was a really good man.

29:55.180 --> 29:56.780
- But he looked like me.

29:56.780 --> 29:59.620
- And now he's dead, not because of
Daniel, because of YOU, Charlie!

29:59.620 --> 30:03.900
- But he looked like me!
- No, it's all right, mate.

30:03.900 --> 30:05.980
No, she's lying.

30:05.980 --> 30:08.820
Yeah. Yeah, we both know she's a
liar.

30:08.820 --> 30:11.660
I don't think she can help it.

30:11.660 --> 30:13.580
[HICKS GROANS IN PAIN]

30:13.580 --> 30:15.180
- Run!

30:22.500 --> 30:24.820
- Daniel! Stop!

30:30.180 --> 30:32.340
[RENKO MOANS IN PAIN]

30:39.540 --> 30:41.940
Daniel! Stop!

31:21.860 --> 31:24.060
[HICKS GRUNTS AND COUGHS]

31:27.860 --> 31:30.820
- She was lying.

31:30.820 --> 31:32.500
He was my dad.

31:35.260 --> 31:37.740
- I know. I know, mate.

31:55.900 --> 31:58.260
[MOBILE PHONE RINGS]

32:01.860 --> 32:06.860
- You catch him?
- Not yet. But I will.
- No, you won't.

32:06.860 --> 32:09.980
- What, is that supposed be some
sort of a threat?

32:09.980 --> 32:13.140
You've got no cards to play here,
mate.
- You think?

32:13.140 --> 32:16.620
- If you had anything on Alex Butler
- anything at all -

32:16.620 --> 32:19.340
I'd know about it by now.
- But what about his wife?

32:19.340 --> 32:22.020
- What, you think Mari's going to
believe any of your paranoid

32:22.020 --> 32:24.700
- bullshit?
- What I mean is,

32:24.700 --> 32:28.260
how's everyone going to react to
know that you're screwing her?

32:29.460 --> 32:31.820
I mean, Charlie Hicks, right?

32:31.820 --> 32:34.380
He's not perfect but, Christ
almighty, he's loyal.

32:34.380 --> 32:38.100
So what will they think? Mishal,
Herbie, George, Keith.

32:38.100 --> 32:40.220
I mean, that's bad enough...

32:42.060 --> 32:44.220
..but what about Simone and Hailey?

32:47.060 --> 32:49.020
[PHONE VIBRATES]

33:00.220 --> 33:02.460
You get away from my house.

33:02.460 --> 33:04.500
- I can take it all away.

33:04.500 --> 33:06.820
All the people you love.

33:06.820 --> 33:08.820
I can make them detest you,

33:08.820 --> 33:10.900
and you'll have no-one.

33:10.900 --> 33:13.740
- What, so I get a taste of what
it's like to be you?

33:13.740 --> 33:15.820
- Don't pretend you're not
terrified.

33:15.820 --> 33:17.540
- See, the funny thing is, Elaine,

33:17.540 --> 33:21.660
that you think you understand me so
well.

33:21.660 --> 33:24.420
But you don't even understand
yourself.

33:24.420 --> 33:26.580
See, the thing about loving someone
-

33:26.580 --> 33:30.540
and I mean really loving someone -

33:30.540 --> 33:33.420
is that it's not about them liking
you.

33:33.420 --> 33:37.020
It's about doing what's best for
them,

33:37.020 --> 33:38.900
no matter the cost.

33:40.220 --> 33:42.140
I mean, look at yourself.

33:42.140 --> 33:45.860
Look at what you're doing right now.

33:45.860 --> 33:48.620
- I mean, that's love, that is.
- Stay away from my son.

33:48.620 --> 33:51.860
- He's a murderer!
- There's a lot of them around, and
in a few months

33:51.860 --> 33:54.540
it's not going to matter who's a
killer and who's not.

33:54.540 --> 33:57.580
- You say one word to Simone...

33:57.580 --> 33:59.780
..one word...

33:59.780 --> 34:04.100
- and I will end you.
- That's big words, Charlie.

34:04.100 --> 34:06.060
- No, no, no, no.

34:06.060 --> 34:08.380
We're in a whole other level now.

34:08.380 --> 34:10.139
You've just taken this to a new
place.

34:10.139 --> 34:11.739
I mean, they send you after me,

34:11.739 --> 34:14.139
what do I care? You're no threat to
me.

34:14.139 --> 34:16.780
It's not even like I don't like you,
because basically I do,

34:16.780 --> 34:19.500
but if you take this to Simone and

34:19.500 --> 34:22.580
Hailey, I will kill you, stone dead.

34:22.580 --> 34:26.179
I will finish you!

34:26.179 --> 34:28.060
- Five years, Charlie.

34:28.060 --> 34:30.300
Leave my son alone.

35:05.300 --> 35:07.660
[DOOR IS UNLOCKED]

35:09.860 --> 35:12.220
[DISTANT SIREN]

35:12.220 --> 35:15.020
- Is Stef here?

35:15.020 --> 35:17.100
- Who?

35:17.100 --> 35:18.740
- Stefan?

36:04.900 --> 36:06.860
Stef.

36:09.420 --> 36:11.340
Stef.

36:11.340 --> 36:13.460
- You know him?
- Yeah.

36:16.500 --> 36:18.220
Just wanted to stay for a bit.

36:19.740 --> 36:21.820
- So stay for a bit.

36:42.140 --> 36:44.500
[MOBILE PHONE RINGS]

36:47.420 --> 36:49.900
Hey! Listen, I can't talk right now.

36:49.900 --> 36:52.180
I'm having a bit of a day here.

36:52.180 --> 36:54.660
- She's pregnant!

36:56.660 --> 36:58.380
- Well, who told you?

36:58.380 --> 36:59.940
Was it Elaine?

36:59.940 --> 37:01.900
- No-one told me anything, that's
the point!

37:01.900 --> 37:04.940
- Well, how'd you find out?
- Like that's what matters?!
- Look, I just...

37:04.940 --> 37:07.380
Sorry, look, I'm trying to follow
you here, all right?

37:07.380 --> 37:09.420
I'm... I'm not following.

37:09.420 --> 37:11.700
- Simone came round.

37:11.700 --> 37:15.620
- What for?
- She wanted me to talk to you.

37:15.620 --> 37:17.740
- About?
- Alex.

37:19.060 --> 37:21.780
- Look, I don't get it. What did she
want you to say?

37:21.780 --> 37:24.700
- She knows something's wrong!

37:24.700 --> 37:26.820
She's scared for you.

37:31.740 --> 37:33.620
Listen...

37:36.220 --> 37:40.060
I know we've never spoken about it,
because we can't...

37:40.060 --> 37:42.220
..but I do know what you did for
us...

37:43.620 --> 37:45.460
..and I know what it cost you.

37:47.060 --> 37:49.620
I know it every second of every day.

37:51.700 --> 37:56.060
But Simone asked me to talk to you,
your wife...

37:58.660 --> 38:00.620
..so now I'm talking to you.

38:05.500 --> 38:08.820
This has got to end, me and you.

38:11.180 --> 38:14.260
It's not good, it's not healthy.

38:14.260 --> 38:16.940
You need to be a husband to your
wife

38:16.940 --> 38:18.620
and a father to your kids.

38:19.940 --> 38:21.820
And I need...

38:23.300 --> 38:25.900
- What? What do you need?

38:30.940 --> 38:32.540
- I need to be clear of it.

38:34.780 --> 38:38.180
I need to stop looking back and
start looking towards the future.

38:39.620 --> 38:42.100
- Yeah, well, what future?

38:42.100 --> 38:44.540
- What, I can't have a future
without you?

38:44.540 --> 38:47.140
- No, sorry, listen, Mari, that's
not what I meant! It's not...

38:47.140 --> 38:48.900
Mari, listen! Mari!

39:43.940 --> 39:45.900
[PHONE ACTIVATES]

39:48.500 --> 39:50.060
- Herbie.

39:54.060 --> 39:55.860
[HE GROANS]

39:57.580 --> 39:59.980
[MOBILE PHONE RINGS]

40:01.540 --> 40:04.380
All right, good news or I hang up.

40:04.380 --> 40:07.140
- Victim's phone is back on the
grid. We are in business.

40:07.140 --> 40:08.860
- Right, that's great news.

40:08.860 --> 40:11.380
All right, kick bollocks, scramble
everything we've got.

40:11.380 --> 40:13.260
I'll see you there.

40:13.260 --> 40:15.700
I'm having that manky little plum
for my dinner.

40:19.980 --> 40:21.380
- OK, let's go!

40:21.380 --> 40:25.620
- RADIO:
- Whisky three, currently en root to
apprehend. Murder suspect,

40:25.620 --> 40:28.180
potentially armed and dangerous.

40:28.180 --> 40:30.620
Armed response unit requested.

40:30.620 --> 40:33.140
Proceeding to 13 Lombard Close.

40:33.140 --> 40:35.780
Echo, one, three, Romeo, Charlie.

40:37.940 --> 40:40.620
- Which unit's closest?

40:40.620 --> 40:43.300
All right, tell her to get there as
soon as possible.

40:43.300 --> 40:44.820
We're en route.

40:53.260 --> 40:55.820
- Hey. I'm looking for Daniel.

40:58.580 --> 41:01.420
- I don't know any Daniels. Sorry.

41:01.420 --> 41:03.340
- Do you mind if I pop in,

41:03.340 --> 41:05.660
have a look around, see if he's
here?

41:13.860 --> 41:15.460
Hey, Daniel.

41:16.540 --> 41:18.140
How are you?

41:21.980 --> 41:24.340
Can you tell me where it is, Daniel?

41:24.340 --> 41:26.620
Can you help me find a flash drive?

41:34.740 --> 41:37.580
Did you hide it somewhere?

41:37.580 --> 41:39.660
Give it to someone?

41:43.580 --> 41:46.940
Did you give it to Elaine?

41:46.940 --> 41:49.780
Is that what you did? You gave it to
your mum?

41:56.020 --> 41:58.500
That was good, Daniel.

41:58.500 --> 42:00.300
Very clever thinking.

42:05.260 --> 42:07.540
Can I get some more of what he's
having?

42:09.340 --> 42:12.300
- How much more?

42:12.300 --> 42:14.180
- A lot.

42:33.140 --> 42:35.620
[SIRENS]

42:49.340 --> 42:51.580
- Sshhh. It's OK.

42:51.580 --> 42:53.060
Sshhh.

42:53.060 --> 42:55.100
[TYRES SCREECH]

43:03.180 --> 43:05.260
[LINE RINGING]

43:05.260 --> 43:08.060
- Renko's here for the boy. She's
got the flash drive.

43:08.060 --> 43:11.380
- Control the situation. We'll be
there shortly.

43:11.380 --> 43:13.020
- Roger that.

43:13.020 --> 43:15.460
- Herbie, how long before armed
response are on the scene?

43:15.460 --> 43:17.460
- ETA seven minutes. Where are you?

43:17.460 --> 43:19.380
- I'm en route.

43:19.380 --> 43:22.100
I'll be there in ten, they'll have
to start without me.

43:30.260 --> 43:32.340
Where's Daniel?

43:32.340 --> 43:34.340
[SHE GRUNTS]

43:39.660 --> 43:41.900
[GUN CLICKS]

43:48.900 --> 43:51.820
- What did you give him?
- Enough.

43:52.900 --> 43:55.260
But he can still live.

43:55.260 --> 43:59.140
There's still time, if you can keep
him awake,

43:59.140 --> 44:02.220
get him to Accident and Emergency
and give him a shot of naloxone.

44:04.340 --> 44:06.100
You know what I want.

44:09.340 --> 44:12.540
Give me that flash drive and he's
all yours.

44:16.500 --> 44:18.740
- So you'll just let me take him?
- Absolutely.

44:18.740 --> 44:21.100
- And I believe that?
- Why not?

44:21.100 --> 44:23.780
I'll have forgotten you both by
tea-time.

44:32.620 --> 44:34.140
- OK.

44:36.180 --> 44:38.420
- How do we do it?
- Have you got it on you?

44:38.420 --> 44:40.020
- In my pocket.

44:40.020 --> 44:42.300
- Reach into your pocket.

44:42.300 --> 44:44.180
Move slowly.

44:45.180 --> 44:47.060
Throw it to me.

44:47.060 --> 44:48.380
Underarm.

45:14.340 --> 45:17.500
- Daniel, Daniel, you stay awake,
OK?

45:17.500 --> 45:20.740
I'm getting you out of here but we
need that phone.

45:20.740 --> 45:23.100
Daniel, it's got your fingerprints
on it. Your DNA.

45:23.100 --> 45:25.020
Wake up! Where's the phone?

45:27.900 --> 45:30.300
30 seconds, we're leaving. Stay
awake!

45:34.380 --> 45:35.660
[DOOR SLAMS]

45:37.500 --> 45:38.700
- Phone.

45:40.220 --> 45:41.540
- What phone?

45:45.900 --> 45:49.380
- That's all I've got. So take it
and give me the phone.

45:50.780 --> 45:52.020
- And your cards.

45:52.020 --> 45:53.340
- Take it and give me the phone

45:53.340 --> 45:55.900
and I'll let you leave this shitbox
with the use of your limbs.

46:04.820 --> 46:06.700
- Mishal? He's powered off his
phone.

46:06.700 --> 46:08.980
- He may be moving on.
- We're five minutes out.

46:08.980 --> 46:11.020
[SIREN WAILS]

46:22.180 --> 46:23.900
[TYRES SCREECH OUTSIDE]

46:36.420 --> 46:38.100
[MEN GRUNT]

46:49.300 --> 46:50.940
What's this?

46:50.940 --> 46:52.980
Hey, I said that I would take care
of it.

46:52.980 --> 46:55.460
- And so you did. Now it's time for
us to take over.

46:55.460 --> 46:56.780
- There's no time for this!

46:56.780 --> 46:58.500
Look, Armed Response are on their
way!

46:58.500 --> 47:01.100
- Then follow procedure and wait for
them to arrive.

47:02.220 --> 47:04.340
This will all be over in a moment,
Charlie.

47:06.180 --> 47:08.060
[SHOUTING]

47:16.980 --> 47:18.700
[TASER CRACKLES]

47:23.860 --> 47:26.620
[VOICES ECHO AND FADE]

47:30.060 --> 47:31.300
What happens to Elaine?

47:32.340 --> 47:36.540
- We retrieve the flash drive, after
which she's no threat

47:36.540 --> 47:39.300
and therefore of no interest.

47:39.300 --> 47:43.100
In a minute or two, the police will
arrive to find that Elaine has been
protecting her son.

47:43.100 --> 47:46.140
She'll be arrested and charged with
- I don't know -

47:46.140 --> 47:47.660
withholding evidence?

47:47.660 --> 47:50.100
Perverting the course of justice?

47:51.420 --> 47:53.100
- You've set her up pretty nicely.

47:54.900 --> 47:56.620
And what about Daniel?

47:59.020 --> 48:01.220
- Just let her dig her own grave,
Charlie.

48:41.180 --> 48:42.420
- It's not here.

48:44.980 --> 48:49.420
- Tell me where it is, or I'll have
to let Daniel pass away.

48:51.660 --> 48:54.860
His breathing's very shallow. It
won't be long now.

48:54.860 --> 48:57.300
- Well, that's your plan anyway,
isn't it?

48:57.300 --> 48:59.700
Get what you want. Kill us, cover
your tracks.

49:00.860 --> 49:02.660
- It doesn't have to be that way.

49:04.700 --> 49:06.060
Your time is up.

49:06.060 --> 49:07.660
I think we both know that.

49:07.660 --> 49:09.540
But I don't see any reason

49:09.540 --> 49:12.060
why Daniel can't live.

49:18.740 --> 49:20.820
[BRAKES SCREECH]

49:31.460 --> 49:33.180
[HE CHANGES GEAR]

49:33.180 --> 49:35.540
- If you hurt me, or my son,

49:35.540 --> 49:38.260
your dirty secret's all over the
newspapers tonight.

49:39.900 --> 49:41.980
- I've been doing this a long time,
Elaine.

49:43.180 --> 49:45.420
I know a bluff when I see one.

49:45.420 --> 49:48.140
You've had no time to do anything
clever with the file.

49:48.140 --> 49:50.860
So it's no longer in play, is it?

49:55.620 --> 49:57.980
I think we're probably done here.

49:57.980 --> 50:00.220
Take her back for interrogation.

50:00.220 --> 50:03.180
Leave the boy here. His story is
over.

50:08.380 --> 50:11.340
- No, no, no, no, no!

50:11.340 --> 50:12.460
Daniel!

50:12.460 --> 50:13.700
Just don't!

50:13.700 --> 50:15.740
No!

50:15.740 --> 50:17.620
Daniel! No!

50:33.100 --> 50:35.940
- Oh, no! Look!

50:35.940 --> 50:37.420
There's no way out!

50:37.420 --> 50:39.660
[DISTANT SIRENS]

50:39.660 --> 50:42.900
Except that noise you're hearing is
a specialist firearms unit,

50:42.900 --> 50:44.620
tooled up with semi-automatics.

50:45.860 --> 50:48.380
Now, you see, if that lot see you
lot

50:48.380 --> 50:51.180
with a gun to a police officer's
skull,

50:51.180 --> 50:53.180
they will shoot you dead ten times
over.

50:56.180 --> 50:57.900
Now, I don't care who you are.

50:59.020 --> 51:00.660
I don't care who you work for.

51:01.700 --> 51:03.460
You don't get to kill children.

51:05.820 --> 51:07.060
Not even mad ones.

51:09.620 --> 51:13.060
So go on, hop in your wanker tanker
and piss off!

51:25.180 --> 51:27.060
[SIRENS APPROACH]

51:27.060 --> 51:28.420
Here they come.

51:31.380 --> 51:32.580
Ready or not.

51:46.260 --> 51:47.620
- Armed police!

51:49.700 --> 51:51.260
- Armed police!

51:53.140 --> 51:55.580
- Armed police!
- Armed police! Do not move!

51:59.380 --> 52:01.620
- Daniel! Stay with us, mate!

52:01.620 --> 52:04.140
All right, you hear me? You stay
with us!

52:04.140 --> 52:06.660
- Stay with me, OK? Stay with me!

52:06.660 --> 52:09.900
- Do not fall asleep, you understand
me?!

52:09.900 --> 52:13.420
♪ The Queen was in the parlour
Eating all the honey!

52:13.420 --> 52:16.540
♪ The King was in the chambermaid
And she was in the money... ♪

52:16.540 --> 52:20.100
- Wake up, wake up, wake up!
- ♪ Balls to your partner, backs
against the wall...

52:20.100 --> 52:23.500
♪ If you can't get laid on a
Saturday night, you'll never get
laid at all! ♪

52:23.500 --> 52:25.700
Stay with us, Daniel!

52:27.860 --> 52:30.420
♪ Balls to your partner, backs
against the wall,

52:30.420 --> 52:34.060
♪ If you can't get laid on a
Saturday night, you'll never get
laid at all! ♪

52:49.220 --> 52:51.660
- Hey.
- Hi.

52:51.660 --> 52:52.860
- Any news?

52:53.900 --> 52:55.260
- He's going to be all right.

52:57.700 --> 52:59.060
Well, let's be fair -

52:59.060 --> 53:02.180
I don't know what "all right"
actually means in this context.

53:02.180 --> 53:04.740
- Hey, listen, it's not his fault.

53:04.740 --> 53:06.260
You know, the kid's...

53:08.260 --> 53:10.660
Well, he's ill.

53:10.660 --> 53:14.180
We'll take him back to the Secure
Unit. We'll tell them...

53:15.260 --> 53:19.420
..I don't know, we found him
sleeping rough at Victoria Station
or something.

53:19.420 --> 53:20.740
- OK.

53:23.020 --> 53:24.580
And what about his dad?

53:25.900 --> 53:27.300
Noah?

53:33.660 --> 53:35.860
- Yeah, well, we'll think of
something.

53:36.980 --> 53:38.740
- And us?

53:38.740 --> 53:41.540
You do know she's going to come for
us twice as hard.

53:42.660 --> 53:45.260
- Yeah, well, not if we've still got
that flash drive.

53:54.260 --> 53:55.500
No!

53:57.060 --> 53:58.260
No, no.

53:58.260 --> 54:00.020
I keep my spare keys in that.

54:00.020 --> 54:01.500
- I know.

54:01.500 --> 54:02.700
- That is cheeky.

54:06.100 --> 54:07.420
But good.

54:09.260 --> 54:10.580
Very good.

54:18.380 --> 54:19.540
- Charlie...

54:22.540 --> 54:23.940
You told me once...

54:27.100 --> 54:29.940
You said you'd protect Daniel if I
wasn't about.

54:32.500 --> 54:33.900
- Yeah, I know.

54:35.180 --> 54:36.940
- I thought you were threatening me.

54:40.060 --> 54:41.460
- I know.

54:44.460 --> 54:45.700
- I'm so sorry.

54:47.580 --> 54:49.060
- Hey, come on, don't be.

54:53.420 --> 54:55.420
Look, you and me...

54:55.420 --> 54:57.420
It doesn't mean you're not a
problem.

54:58.580 --> 55:02.940
You're just a problem I have to deal
with in my own way. OK?

55:05.700 --> 55:07.940
- But I got you so wrong from day
one.

55:07.940 --> 55:10.140
- Well, I don't know about that.

55:10.140 --> 55:12.860
- I honestly thought they were
right.

55:12.860 --> 55:14.300
Before I got to know you.

55:15.700 --> 55:17.380
I thought you killed Butler.

55:25.860 --> 55:27.860
- Elaine, I... I thought you knew.

55:33.980 --> 55:35.300
- Knew what, Charlie?

55:51.700 --> 55:52.980
- It was me.

